com.cerner.bunsen.definitions

Class FhirConversionSupport

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cerner.bunsen.definitions.FhirConversionSupport
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Stu3FhirConversionSupport

    public abstract class FhirConversionSupport
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Helper functions to allow code to convert FHIR resources independently of the FHIR version. Typically an implementation specific to a FHIR version is provided at runtime.

      • compositeValues

        public abstract Map<String,List> compositeValues(org.hl7.fhir.instance.model.api.IBase composite)
        Returns a map of the fields in a composite type to the corresponding values. Since FHIR fields may have multiple values a list is returned, and single-valued items will have a singleton list.
        Parameters:
        composite - a FHIR composite type
        Returns:
        a map of field names to the values.
